-- Deutsche Telekom Will Cut 1,300 Jobs Without Firings, FAS Says
-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 2012-06-23T14:22:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-23/deutsche-telekom-will-cut-1-300-jobs-without-firings-fas-says.html
Deutsche Telekom AG (DTE)  plans to cut
1,300 positions at its headquarters by 2015 without firing
workers,  Frankfurter Allgemeine Sonntagszeitung  reported, citing
an interview with Marion Schick, the board member responsible
for human resources.  The company will shift some tasks away from the
headquarters to local offices, the newspaper cited Schick as
saying in an e-mailed preview of an interview to be published
tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naomi Kresge in Berlin at 
 nkresge@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at 
 pserafino@bloomberg.net  